# tokyo-listings Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from all feature plans. Last updated: 2026-04-05

## Active Technologies

- TypeScript (strict), Node.js 22 LTS for Next.js; **Bun 1.2.x** (e.g. 1.2.23) for package manager + Next.js (App Router), **Uniwind** + **Tailwind v4** + **[Rosé Pine for Tailwind](https://github.com/rose-pine/tailwind-css)** (`react-native` + `react-native-web` + `@expo/next-adapter`), tRPC, TanStack Query, Jotai, Hono, (001-tokyo-listings-baseline). Avoid **Bun 1.3.11** for day-to-day installs on this repo — see **Bun / `bun install`** below.

## Project Structure

```text
apps/web/
apps/api/
  src/
  test/          # mirrors src/ — *.test.ts live here, not under src/
packages/db/
packages/scraping/
  src/
  test/          # mirrors src/; fixtures under test/fixtures/
```

Automated tests for app and package code use a sibling **`test/`** tree that **mirrors** **`src/`**
(same relative paths). Do not add colocated `*.test.ts` under `src/`. API unit tests live under
`apps/api/test/`, not a separate repo-root `tests/` folder.

## Commands

bun run test && bun run lint

## Docker Compose (primary integration check)

After implementing or changing features that touch **API, web, DB, or Dockerfiles**, **verify the full stack** unless blocked (e.g. missing secrets only the operator can add):

1. From the **repository root**: `docker compose build` (or `docker compose build --no-cache` when images must not use stale layers) then `docker compose up -d`.
2. Root **`.env`** must exist with at least **`BETTER_AUTH_SECRET`**, **`GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_SERVER`** (geocode) and **`GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_CLIENT`** (Maps JS), and DB/auth URLs as in **`.env.template`**. If a required secret is missing, say so and stop short of claiming Compose is green.
3. Quick smoke: `GET http://localhost:4001/health`, open **`http://localhost:3000`** (login/map/listings as relevant).

Do **not** start a second Compose project on the same host ports (5432 / 4001 / 3000); bring any older stack down first. Postgres data persists in the **`tokyo-listings_postgres_data`** volume unless `docker compose down -v` is used.

